 <DOC> <DOCNO> LA050889-0075 </DOCNO> <DOCID> 54283 </DOCID> <DATE> <P> May 8, 1989, Monday, Home Edition </P> </DATE> <SECTION> <P> Sports; Part 3; Page 7; Column 1; Sports Desk </P> </SECTION> <LENGTH> <P> 691 words </P> </LENGTH> <HEADLINE> <P> LONG BEACH MARATHON; </P> <P> WILSON, YANMIN HAVE THE PATIENCE TO WIN WITH COURSE RECORDS </P> </HEADLINE> <BYLINE> <P> By JULIE CART, Times Staff Writer </P> </BYLINE> <TEXT> <P> Patience is often difficult to muster for those who run the 26.2 miles of a marathon.
 Yanmin broke the old record of 2:44:51 set last year by Dianne Rodgers. </P> <P> Robert Molinatti of Huntington Beach won the wheelchair division in 1:47:59. </P> <P> Run as a race within a race was the Pacific Rim Marathon, which consists of teams from invited countries.
